sharding vs partitioning
-> https://hazelcast.com/glossary/sharding/#:~:text=Sharding%20and%20partitioning%20are%20both,within%20a%20single%20database%20instance.

paritioning referes to breakup within same physical machine generally and sharding is always talked about for different physical machine.
sharding is talked about in cases of vertical and horizontal scaling.
(This is because sharding and partitioning are both related to breaking up a large data set into smaller subsets.
The difference is that sharding implies the data is spread across multiple computers while partitioning does not.
)

->https://www.singlestore.com/blog/database-sharding-vs-partitioning-whats-the-difference/


